<div class="content">
	<p>In addition to being about to customize the visual appearance, you can also customize <%= application.name %>'s sonic characteristics. </p>

	<ol>
		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-cog"></i>Sound Settings</h2>
			<p>The sound settings are controlled through the <a href="#apps/settings-manager">Settings Manager</a> app. To view and change the sound settings, click on the tab labelled "Sound". </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/customizing-environment/customizing-sounds/sound-settings.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title='"Sound" Tab on the System Settings App'><img class="dialog" src="images/help/customizing-environment/customizing-sounds/sound-settings.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">"Sound" Tab on the System Settings App</div>
			</div>

			<p>You will see a list of settings where each system event type is matched with a sound to be played when that event occurs. You can also select no sound, if you prefer this event to be silent. </p>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-volume-up"></i>Sound Event Types</h2>		
			<p>The system event types that you can configure to play a sound are the following: </p>

			<ul>
				<li>
					<label>Session Events</label><br />
					login, logout
				</li>

				<li>
					<label>Edit Events</label><br />
					cut, copy, paste, duplicate, delete
				</li>

				<li>
					<label>Window Events</label><br />
					open, minimize, maximize, restore, close
				</li>

				<li>
					<label>File Events</label><br />
					new, move, drop, recycle, upload, download, compress, extract
				</li>

				<li>
					<label>Interaction Events</label><br />
					zoom-in, zoom-out, tap, send, error
				</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
</div>